<section>
  <h2>Theme Switcher component</h2>
  <p>Accessible theme dropdown with <strong>System</strong> option (follows OS light/dark), <strong>Dark themes</strong> and <strong>Light themes</strong> sections (labels and underlines on mobile), a unique icon per theme (Owl, Palette, Flame, Sunset, Zap, Shield, Heart, Sun, Cake, Lemon, Rainbow, Leaf, Cherry, Brush), and preview on hover. The docs site uses the <strong>Astro</strong> Theme Switcher inside Settings. Theme data is shared via <code>src/config/themes.ts</code>; in Svelte you can use the same CSS and the same theme IDs (<code>data-theme</code>).</p>
  <p><a href="/docs/components/theme-switcher">Astro Theme Switcher documentation</a> — usage and keyboard support.</p>
  <p><a href="/docs/svelte/components">← Back to Svelte components</a></p>
</section>
